Program: Letter from America by Alistair Cooke
Title: Etiquette for presidential candidates and the heat wave of Summer 1988
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00ydry9
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 2 Sep 1988
Remembering when presidential candidates only spoke about policy, and when Adlai Stephenson broke the rule. And could the hot summer be the result of greenhouse gases?